Aim: To apply the Hierarchical clustering algorithm on a dataset and analyze how the data instances are grouped
based on similarity using WEKA.
Tool Used:
Software: Weka (Waikato Environment for Knowledge Analysis).
Operating System: Windows / Linux
 Algorithm Used: K-Means Clustering (SimpleKMeans in WEKA)
Dataset Used:
The dataset used is glass.arff from the WEKA data repository.
The Glass Dataset contains chemical composition data of different types of glass. Each instance represents a
glass sample with attributes such as refractive index and concentrations of elements like sodium, magnesium,
aluminum, silicon, potassium, calcium, barium, and iron.
The dataset contains 214 instances and 10 attributes, making it suitable for clustering experiments. It is
commonly used to analyze and group glass samples based on their chemical properties.
