Conclusion :
The hierarchical clustering experiment was successfully performed using the HierarchicalClusterer algorithm in
WEKA. The Glass Dataset was used for this experiment, which contains information about the chemical
composition of different glass samples.The algorithm grouped similar glass samples based on their attribute
similarities and formed clusters in a hierarchical tree structure. This method helped in understanding the
relationships among the data instances by progressively merging similar clusters.Thus, the experiment
demonstrates that Hierarchical Clustering is an effective unsupervised learning technique for discovering
patterns and grouping similar data points in a dataset.
